<p><a name="Notes_and_references" id="Notes_and_references"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Persistence_of_vision&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Notes and references">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes and references</span></h2>
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> Wertheimer, 1912. Experimentelle Studien über das Sehen von Bewegung. Zeitschrift für Psychologie 61, pp. 161–265</li>
<li id="cite_note-Coltheart-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Coltheart_1-0" title="">^</a></b> Coltheart M. "The persistences of vision." <i>Philos Trans R Soc Lond B Biol Sci.</i> 1980 Jul 8;290(1038):57-69. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6106242" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6106242">PMID 6106242</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Anderson1993-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Anderson1993_2-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFAnderson.2C_Joseph.3B_Anderson.2C_Barbara1993">Anderson, Joseph; Anderson, Barbara (1993). "<a href="http://www.uca.edu/org/ccsmi/ccsmi/classicwork/Myth%20Revisited.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.uca.edu/org/ccsmi/ccsmi/classicwork/Myth%20Revisited.htm" rel="nofollow">The Myth of Persistence of Vision Revisited</a>". <i>Journal of Film and Video</i> <b>45</b> (1): 3–12<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.uca.edu/org/ccsmi/ccsmi/classicwork/Myth%20Revisited.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.uca.edu/org/ccsmi/ccsmi/classicwork/Myth%20Revisited.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.uca.edu/org/ccsmi/ccsmi/classicwork/Myth%20Revisited.htm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Myth+of+Persistence+of+Vision+Revisited&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Film+and+Video&amp;rft.aulast=Anderson%2C+Joseph%3B+Anderson%2C+Barbara&amp;rft.au=Anderson%2C+Joseph%3B+Anderson%2C+Barbara&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.volume=45&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=3%E2%80%9312&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.uca.edu%2Forg%2Fccsmi%2Fccsmi%2Fclassicwork%2FMyth%2520Revisited.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Persistence_of_vision"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> Actually 60 images per 1001ms, commonly rounded to 59.94 or 60 for discussion.</li>
